A Multi-Taal Log-Based MIDI Composition System
🧬 SYSTEM OVERVIEW (V1)
The Orbit House Engine is a modular rhythmic composition framework that converts cyclical time systems into MIDI-based groove structures.
It is built on:
Layered log drum architecture (Amapiano core)
Multi-taal rhythm mapping (Teentaal, Jhaptal, Misra Chapu)
32-step hybrid grid system
JSON-based pattern logic
Python MIDI generation engine
🧠 V1 DESIGN PRINCIPLE
Rhythm is a system of interacting time cycles, not a fixed loop.
All musical output is generated from:
Time cycles
Layer roles
Grid mapping logic
Controlled variation systems
NOT from fixed beat patterns.
