🔊 CORE SOUND ARCHITECTURE
🎛 1. Log System (Amapiano Core)
🔊 Sub Log (Anchor Layer)
Low-frequency time stabilizer
Defines structural downbeats
Minimal variation design
🥁 Rhythm Log (Groove Engine)
Mid-frequency rhythmic driver
Creates syncopation and bounce
Main movement generator
✨ Accent Log (Variation Layer)
High-frequency rhythmic decoration
Fill generation system
Controlled unpredictability
(Optional Expansion in V1.1)
Sync Log (displacement layer)
Ghost Log (micro-rhythm layer)
⏱ RHYTHM TIME SYSTEMS
🇿🇦 Amapiano Grid System
32-step cycle
2-bar structure
3+3+2 displacement feel (tresillo influence)
Medium-loose swing (55–62%)
🇮🇳 Teentaal System
16-beat symmetrical cycle
Used as structural reference grid
Maps directly to 16-step MIDI resolution
🇮🇳 Jhaptal System
10-beat asymmetrical cycle
Used for controlled rhythmic tension
Mapped via expanded step projection
🇮🇳 Misra Chapu System
7-beat fluid cycle
Used for variation and fill logic
Acts as overlay modulation system
🔁 MULTI-TAAL ENGINE LOGIC
All systems are unified through:
Cycle → Grid Projection → MIDI Event Mapping
🧩 Interaction Modes
🎛 Single Mode
One cycle active:
Pure Teentaal OR Amapiano OR Jhaptal
🎛 Dual Mode
Two interacting systems:
Example: Teentaal + Amapiano
Example: Jhaptal + Log Engine
Creates:
rhythmic tension
groove hybridisation
🎛 Full Engine Mode (4-Log System)
Amapiano architecture layer applied across any cycle system:
Sub = anchor
Rhythm = motion
Accent = variation
(optional sync layer in V1.1)
